    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Artists, usually printmakers or painters, who specialize in Ukioyo-e, a genre that developed in the Edo period, Japan, and is characterized by a mixture of the realistic narrative of brothels, kabuki theaters, and other such places, with a distinctive decorative style.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
